data.name: Label5.Text
data.value: Underneath each week column, detailed statistics provide insight on the cost of labor for each day of the week, the number of employees scheduled to work each day, the percent of labor costs that that particular day represents, and the number of hours in that particular workday. This allows managers to view the effect of efficient employee scheduling in real time as demand changes.

data.name: Label2.Text
data.value: Swift's dashboard is where all employee scheduling is aggregated into a large, easy to view calendar. Using a series of optimization models, Swift determines which employees should work on which days throughout the next week based on the business' demand, shift rankings by employees, and salaries. To view more information on a given day, simply click the column header or anywhere inside the column box to display more information in the left-hand sidebar.

data.name: Label13.Text
data.value: Shift data can also be easily changed by clicking the "Shifts" button in the taskbar. This will allow managers to change the number of consecutive shifts that the model should assume each employee will work, based on the needs of the business and demand.

data.name: Label11.Text
data.value: Payroll records can be changed with the click of a button, and increased or decreased at any point depending on demand or other factors. This can be done by clicking the "Payroll" button in the taskbar. Once your changes are saved, salary information will be updated for all applicable employees and the model will be re-optimized.

data.name: Label9.Text
data.value: Employees can be added to the system at any time, and will be accounted for once they are entered by re-optimizing the model. Simply click the "Add Employee" button in the taskbar at the top of the screen to complete the task.

data.name: Label7.Text
data.value: Appointments can be added as they come in by clicking the "Add Appointments" button in the taskbar. This will launch a form where the Client Name and Period are taken and added to the database. The model is then re-optimized to reflect changes and ensure the most recent data.
